Description: Lip and wall sherd of East Greek (North Ionian) pottery rosette bowl; interior: orange-fired glaze with added red band lined in white; exterior reserved with band on top of lip and two bands on lower wall and a dark brown line painted at top of rim; small part of a probable rosette preserved at left break; inscription cut on exterior.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis) (said to be)
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.845)
